Reasoning: The paper discusses the recognition and processing of acronyms in news articles, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as entity recognition and linking. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) or Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of evaluation results and statistics, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the adaptation of acronym recognition patterns to the news domain, which could involve neural networks and other techniques used in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
